commit.message: Rough guides for checking that we work on 2/3 & releasing
Bump the version number for a bugfix release

Ensure we work for py2 & py2

Addressing https://github.com/tjguk/wmi/issues/8
Slight tweaks to docs (mostly missing spaces)

Drop an unneeded test for datatypes
Fix a couple of resource warnings
Avoid using winreg.HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE in examples because, on x64, it's got a strange value. Instead, use win32con.HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE which is hardcoded to the right value
Revert to using home-brewed check for equality (which also matches the logic for hash). The CompareTo method doesn't appear to consider equal two instances of the same Operating System!
Fix some indentation issues in the module docstring caused by over-simple PEP8 compliance changes
Add a test for unsigned int
Rework the readme as Restructured Text by copying the index from the underlying docs
Use the correct Method call for CompareTo (a fault hidden by the except AttributeError trap)
Bring Copyright notice up to date
Reinstate the CompareTo logic in __eq__, defaulting to unequal if the other object isn't a WMI instance
Remove space before brackets for PEP8 compliance
